This program is a REST API using Jersey (JAX-RS) to perform CRUD operations on Student data.


---

1. Flow of the Program

Step 1 – Create Dynamic Web Project

1. Open Eclipse IDE


2. Go to File → New → Dynamic Web Project


3. Give project name → RestAPI


4. Select Tomcat Server


5. Click Finish




---

Step 2 – Add Required Libraries

Add the required Jersey JAX-RS libraries to the project.


---

Step 3 – Create Package

Inside src/main/java

Create package:

com.student.api


---

Step 4 – Create Java Class

Create class:

StudentResource.java

This class will implement REST operations:

GET → List students

POST → Add student

PUT → Update student

DELETE → Remove student



---

Step 5 – Configure web.xml

Inside WEB-INF folder create:

web.xml

Configure Jersey servlet.


---

Step 6 – Run the Project

1. Right click project


2. Run on Server


3. Server: Tomcat




---

Step 7 – Test APIs

Use browser or Postman to send requests:

GET

POST

PUT

DELETE



